cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories:

- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a novel matrix factorization model that learns the deviation of data and conducts dynamic reweighting of instances. This is a machine learning problem that falls under the category of supervised learning.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper applies the proposed model to clean recommendation datasets, which is a common problem in information retrieval. The model aims to improve the accuracy of recommendation by emphasizing more on the reliable instances.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a new approach to modeling sample noise and improving the performance of matrix factorization models. This is a topic that falls under the broader category of artificial intelligence.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper applies the proposed model to noisy sensor datasets, which can be seen as a type of social and information network. The model aims to improve the accuracy of sensor data analysis by taking into account the heteroscedastic noise distribution.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new algorithm for matrix factorization that involves dynamic reweighting of instances. This is a topic that falls under the category of data structures and algorithms.
